Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of water with a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil. Pick the @parsley leaves{} from the stems and discard the stems. Cut the @cauliflower{1%head} into bite-sized florets. Toss the cauliflower on one side of a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, until soft and golden brown.

Thinly slice the @shallot{1} into rounds. Smash @garlic{1%clove} with the flat of your #knife{}. Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @red bell pepper{1}, then thinly slice. Halfway through cooking the cauliflower, toss the bell pepper with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on the opposite side of the baking sheet with the cauliflower. Return to the oven for the remaining ~{10-12%minutes}, until soft and slightly charred.

Meanwhile, add the @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup} to the boiling water and cook for ~{7-9%minutes}, until al dente. Drain and rinse under cold water.

Pickle the shallots: in a #small pot{}, bring @red wine vinegar{12.5%milliliters}, the @shallots{}, and @water{1/3%cup} to a boil. Remove from heat and let sit for ~{2-3%minutes} then remove the shallots from the pickling liquid.

== OPTIONAL Romesco Sauce ==

Mince @?garlic{1%clove}. In a #blender{}, blend together the roasted red peppers, @almonds{1%ounce}, minced garlic, @red wine vinegar{12.5%milliliters}, @smoked paprika{1/2%teaspoon}, @water{1/3%cup}, and @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoons}. Blend until smooth, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> The romesco sauce is optional but a delicious twist that takes the meal to the next level.

== Steak ==

Heat @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Season the @sirloin steak{10%ounce} on all sides with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @smoked paprika{1/2%teaspoon}. Add the smashed garlic to the pan and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Remove and discard garlic. Add the steak to the pan and cook for ~{4-7%minutes} per side, until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

== Cauliflower Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together the roasted cauliflower, Israeli couscous, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, parsley leaves, pickled shallot, and, if you did not make the romesco, the roasted red peppers and almonds. Toss with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice the steak against the grain. Serve alongside the cauliflower salad. Drizzle the steak with the romesco sauce (if made) and enjoy!